The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Monday, March 31, 2003  Good Morning Hello It's Monday, March 31, 2003				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	Mayo Road from 11 am. Confederation of West Bengal Trade Association will observe a hungerstrike near the Gandhi statue to protest VAT and other issues. 				 																																	Shyambazar five-point crossing to Raj Bhavan from noon. Traders will form a human chain as part of the protest programme.				 																Music				 																																	A classical vocal recital by writer Amit Chaudhuri at Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre, 6 pm.				 																Talk				 																																	Ananda Reddy of Sri Aurobindo Ashram, Pondicherry, will speak on Essentials of The Gita at Sri Aurobindo Bhavan on 8, Shakespeare Sarani, from 6.15 pm.				 																Dance				 																																	A Maharas recital, organised by Manipuri Nartanashram, at Tagore Research Institute, on 97C, SP Mukherjee Road, 7 pm.				 																Books				 																																	A sale of books, including fiction and non-fiction, at Oxford Bookstore.				 																Art watch				 																																	An exhibition on Forgotten Pioneers of Modern Bengal Art: Radha Charan Bagchi (1910-1977) at Galerie 88 from 3 pm to 7 pm.				 																																	Paintings by Hendrik Wittkopf on display at Max Mueller Bhavan from 3 pm to 8 pm.				 																																	An exhibition of paintings by Chandra Bhattacharjee, Dipak Mukherjee, Goutam Basu, Pramathes Chandra and Ramlal Dhar at Academy of Fine Arts.
